        "from": "payment-service",
        "to": "postgresql",
        "status": "risk",
        "issue": "Connection pool of 10 with no retry logic. Pool exhaustion is a hard failure with no recovery path until connections are returned. 10 connections vs 20 worker threads means the DB is already a bottleneck under normal load."
      }
    ],
    "contract_compliance": "Service contracts are loosely defined. No mention of idempotency keys for Stripe calls, which is critical for retry safety. No dead-letter queue or compensation mechanism for partially-completed payments.",
    "data_flow_integrity": "Critical gap: if a Stripe charge succeeds but the DB write fails (pool exhaustion), the payment is charged but not recorded. No saga pattern or outbox pattern observed to guarantee consistency between Stripe and the local transaction record."
